## üè∑Ô∏è Feld-Naming-Standards

### Prefix-Regel (IMMER befolgen)

| Prefix | Bedeutung | Preset-Quelle |
|--------|-----------|---------------|
| `user_*` | Daten des Users | User Profile |
| `client_*` | Daten des Kunden | Client Preset |
| Kein Prefix | Projekt-spezifisch | Manuell eingeben |

### User Profile Felder

| Feldname | Label | Typ | Beschreibung |
|----------|-------|-----|--------------|
| `user_name` | Your Name | text | Name des Users |
| `user_email` | Your Email | text | E-Mail |
| `user_company` | Your Company | text | Firmenname |
| `user_role` | Your Role | text | Rolle/Titel |
| `user_website` | Your Website | text | Website |
| `user_industry` | Your Industry | text | Branche |
| `user_services` | Your Services | textarea | Leistungen/Angebot |
| `user_tone` | Your Tone | select | Schreibstil |
| `user_differentiator` | Your USP | textarea | Was macht dich anders |

### Client Preset Felder

| Feldname | Label | Typ | Beschreibung |
|----------|-------|-----|--------------|
| `client_name` | Client Name | text | Person f√ºr Content |
| `client_role` | Client Role | text | Rolle der Person |
| `client_company` | Client Company | text | Firmenname |
| `client_website` | Client Website | text | Website |
| `client_industry` | Client Industry | text | Branche |
| `client_contact_name` | Contact Name | text | Ansprechpartner (Billing) |
| `client_contact_email` | Contact Email | text | E-Mail |
| `client_tone` | Client Tone | select | Brand Voice |
| `client_target_audience` | Target Audience | textarea | Zielgruppe |

### Projekt-spezifische Felder (Beispiele)

| Feldname | Wann verwenden |
|----------|----------------|
| `topic` | Thema/Keyword |
| `goal` | Ziel des Outputs |
| `context` | Zus√§tzlicher Kontext |
| `deadline` | Zeitrahmen |
| `budget` | Budget |
| `word_count` | Gew√ºnschte L√§nge |
| `format` | Format-Auswahl |
| `num_items` | Anzahl (z.B. "5 Posts") |

---

## üìù Prompt-Template Standards

### Struktur eines guten Prompts

```markdown
[Kontext: Wer du bist, was du brauchst]

## Input
- Feld 1: {{field_1}}
- Feld 2: {{field_2}}

## Aufgabe
[Klar beschreiben was der Output sein soll]

## Output-Anforderungen
1. [Spezifische Anforderung]
2. [Spezifische Anforderung]
3. [Spezifische Anforderung]

## Format
[Wie der Output strukturiert sein soll]

## Wichtig
- [Kritische Regel 1]
- [Kritische Regel 2]
```

### Quality Requirements (immer einbauen)

**In jedem Prompt-Template m√ºssen Quality Requirements stehen:**

```markdown
## QUALITY REQUIREMENTS
The output MUST:
1. Be immediately usable (no placeholders like [INSERT HERE])
2. Be specific to the inputs provided (not generic)
3. Follow the requested format exactly
4. Be professional and polished
5. [Workflow-spezifische Requirements]
```

### Anti-Patterns (NIEMALS)

| ‚ùå Nicht | ‚úÖ Stattdessen |
|---------|---------------|
| "Give me some ideas for..." | "Create 10 specific [items] with..." |
| "What should I consider..." | "Write the complete [document]..." |
| "Help me think about..." | "Generate the final [output]..." |
| Generische Tipps | Fertiger, spezifischer Output |
| Platzhalter im Output | Vollst√§ndig ausgef√ºllter Output |

