## ‚úÖ Beispiel: Guter Quick Workflow

```json
{
  "slug": "linkedin-post-generator",
  "title": "LinkedIn Post Generator",
  "is_sop": false,
  "workflow_type": "combined",
  "estimated_minutes": 3,
  "time_saved_minutes": 20,
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "prompt",
      "fields": [
        {
          "name": "topic",
          "label": "Post Topic",
          "type": "text",
          "required": true,
          "placeholder": "Lessons from my first failed startup"
        },
        {
          "name": "client_target_audience",
          "label": "Target Audience",
          "type": "text",
          "required": true,
          "placeholder": "B2B founders, startup employees"
        },
        {
          "name": "client_tone",
          "label": "Tone",
          "type": "select",
          "required": true,
          "options": ["Professional", "Casual", "Provocative", "Vulnerable"]
        },
        {
          "name": "goal",
          "label": "Post Goal",
          "type": "select",
          "required": true,
          "options": ["Engagement", "Authority", "Lead Generation", "Hiring"]
        }
      ],
      "prompt_template": "Write a LinkedIn post that's ready to copy and publish.\n\n## Input\n- Topic: {{topic}}\n- Target Audience: {{client_target_audience}}\n- Tone: {{client_tone}}\n- Goal: {{goal}}\n\n## QUALITY REQUIREMENTS\nThe post MUST:\n1. Start with a hook (first line that stops the scroll)\n2. Be 150-200 words (optimal for LinkedIn)\n3. Use short paragraphs (1-2 sentences max)\n4. End with a clear call-to-action or question\n5. NOT use hashtags in the main text (add 3-5 at the very end)\n6. Be ready to post AS-IS (no placeholders)\n\n## Format\n[Hook line]\n\n[2-3 short paragraphs with the story/insight]\n\n[Call-to-action or question]\n\n---\n#hashtag1 #hashtag2 #hashtag3"
    }
  ]
}
```

